{
  "texts": [
    "Let X ∈ R B×d denote the mini-batch of inputs to layer l, with row vectors",
    "We first compute the uncentered covariance matrix",
    "and construct C l by explicitly zeroing the diagonal entries of D:",
    "This removes all self-correlation terms while retaining the pairwise correlations between distinct input dimensions.",
    "The objective is to reduce these off-diagonal correlations without encouraging the trivial all-zero solution."
  ]
}